Citation.sAbstract: The surface tension of the binary refrigerant mixture dimethyl ether (RE170)(1) + propane (R290)(2) at three mass fractions of w1=0.3007,0.4975 and 0.6949 was measured in the temperature range from 243 to 333 K with a differential capillary rise method. The uncertainties of the measurement of the temperature and the surface tension were estimated to be within +-10 mK and +-0.2 mN m-1, respectively. A correlation for the surface tension of the binary refrigerant mixture RE170 + R290 was developed as a function of the composition.
Citation.sTitle: Surface tension of dimethyl ether + propane from 243 to 333 K
